  "id": "MGASA-2018-0256",
  "summary": "Updated python packages fix security vulnerabilities",
  "details": "Updated python packages fix security vulnerabilities:\n\nA flaw was found in the way catastrophic backtracking was implemented\nin Python's pop3lib's apop() method. An attacker could use this flaw to\ncause denial of service (CVE-2018-1060).\n\nA flaw was found in the way catastrophic backtracking was implemented in\nPython's difflib.IS_LINE_JUNK method. An attacker could use this flaw to\ncause denial of service (CVE-2018-1061).\n",
